title: Iranian General ‘Killed by ISIS in Aleppo’
text:
BEIRUT—A senior commander in Iran’s powerful Revolutionary Guard was killed by Islamic State (ISIS) extremists on the outskirts of the northern Syrian city of Aleppo, Iranian state media reported on Friday.
A state television report said that Brig. Gen. Hossein Hamedani was killed in the suburbs of Aleppo while “carrying out an advisory mission.” It didn’t provide any further details. The official IRNA news agency read a statement by...
